    <!-- SECTION 2 — STORY SECTION -->
    <section id="story">
        <span class="section-label">The Logged File</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Synopsis</h2>
        <div class="story-container">
            <div class="synopsis-left">
                <blockquote class="featured-quote">
                    "This place is where the signal died. And that's where I was born."
                </blockquote>
                <div class="synopsis-text">
                    <p>
                        Sushanth Reddy never selected RK Institute of Technology on his counseling preference forms, yet an unexplainable system mismatch logs him officially into the CSE branch. Arriving at the gothic, iron-wrought institution in Andhra Pradesh, he finds himself trapped inside an awkward collegiate ecosystem that hides a terrifying truth.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Alongside his meme-obsessed roommate Arjun and paranormal investigator Nithya, Sushanth uncovers the mystery of E-Block—an abandoned, storm-weathered structure stripped of any modern network reception. Within its dead boundaries, a tragic spectral frequency named Raghu stalks the infrastructure. Reaching out through corrupted walkie-talkies, smartwatches, and offline Java applications, the presence targets those connected to an ancient, fatal mistake.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="themes-wrapper">
                    <h4 class="themes-title">Core Underlying Frequencies</h4>
                    <div class="theme-tags">
                        <span class="theme-tag">Digital Remorse</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Technological Grief</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">Systemic Isolation</span>
                        <span class="theme-tag">The Weight of Silence</span>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="stats-grid">
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">13</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Detailed Chapters</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">3</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Central Investigators</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">72h</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">Phone Seizure Rule</div>
                </div>
                <div class="stat-card">
                    <div class="stat-num">2.37A</div>
                    <div class="stat-label">The Phantom Hour</div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3 — CHARACTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="characters">
        <span class="section-label">Subscribers to the Nightmare</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Persona Database</h2>
        <div class="characters-grid">
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-role">Protagonist</div>
                <h3 class="char-name">Sushanth Reddy</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A pragmatic CSE freshman assigned to RKIT through an inexplicable central system glitch. He inadvertently holds the key to the haunting via his older brother's past collegiate errors.</p>
                <div class="traits-list">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Skeptic</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Targeted</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Logical</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-role">The Catalyst Presence</div>
                <h3 class="char-name">Raghu (Raghuvaran V)</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A talented 2019 batch tech student who transformed into a malicious network frequency after a strict professor confiscated his phone, causing him to miss his parents' dying final call.</p>
                <div class="traits-list">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Digital Entity</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Grief-Driven</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Trapped</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-role">The Investigator</div>
                <h3 class="char-name">Nithya</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">A fearlessly direct ghost blogger residing in the girls' hostel wing. Armed with DSLR setups and EMF meters, she decodes electrical anomalies into systematic active paranormal investigations.</p>
                <div class="traits-list">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Analytical</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Observant</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Bold</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-role">The Comic Safeguard</div>
                <h3 class="char-name">Arjun</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">Sushanth's hyperactive roommate, self-proclaimed prank king, and meme master. Underneath his non-stop humor, he manages proxy servers and builds weaponized microwave EMP blasters.</p>
                <div class="traits-list">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Meme-Generator</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Technician</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Loyal</span>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="character-card">
                <div class="char-role">The Living Regret</div>
                <h3 class="char-name">Karthik R.</h3>
                <p class="char-desc">Sushanth's estranged older brother. As Raghu's former best friend in 2019, he repeatedly dismissed the parental incoming calls as a joke on a smartwatch, initiating the curse.</p>
                <div class="traits-list">
                    <span class="trait-tag">Reclusive</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Haunted</span>
                    <span class="trait-tag">Regretful</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4 — CHAPTERS SECTION -->
    <section id="chapters">
        <span class="section-label">Transmission Logs</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Index of Silence</h2>
        <div class="chapters-grid">
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 01</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Counselling Glitch</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Sushanth is assigned to a completely un-selected college, discovering a dark blood-red warning on the abandoned E-Block walls.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 02</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The E-Block</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The tech professors demonstrate abnormal fear regarding cellular rings, while Sushanth's device registers a sudden offline text alert.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 03</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">One Missed Call</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">At exactly 2:37 AM, an ancient disconnected landline screams to life. Soon after, a devastating digital seizure strikes the computer lab.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 04</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Into the Block</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Under the cover of a loud collegiate tech-fest, the trio ventures deep into E-Block's core, uncovering a terrifying name on a clean chalkboard.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 05</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Ghost in the Signal</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Nithya attempts to capture visual proof of the manifestation, but the camera breaks down as the entity reveals its deep connection to grief.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 06</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Raghu's Story</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">An administrative break-in uncovers disciplinary logs from 2019, revealing how an innocent prank turned into a horrific family tragedy.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 07</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Kill List</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The trio tracks a terrifying pattern of annual occurrences, culminating in a real-time terminal countdown tracking Sushanth's family.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 08</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Trapped by a Ghost</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">As every speaker and earbud across the hostel corridors rings in unison, Sushanth logs out and departs for Karimnagar to track his brother.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 09</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Living Call</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">A tense household confrontation triggers environmental anomalies as the phantom frequency explicitly demands a long-overdue word.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 10</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Ringtone of Death</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The call status reads answered, but a terrifying voicemail confirms that other un-replied souls across major urban networks are awakening.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 11</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Breakdown</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">Nithya monitors dark web trackers showing severe audio anomalies popping up instantly across Mumbai, Kolkata, and Hyderabad.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 12</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">Viral Haunting</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">The campus data framework suffers a total blackout. The investigators construct an analog signal disruptor to cut the source code forever.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="chapter-card">
                <div class="chap-header">
                    <span class="chap-num">Chapter 13</span>
                    <h3 class="chap-title">The Last Goodbye</h3>
                </div>
                <p class="chap-teaser">An intense EMP blast clears the airwaves, letting a vulnerable 2019 voice memo finish its message, establishing quiet closure.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5 — QUOTES SECTION -->
    <section id="quotes">
        <span class="section-label">Intercepted Transmissions</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">Memorable Inscriptions</h2>
        <div class="quotes-container">
            <div class="quotes-featured-box">
                <p class="quote-main-text">"You never forget the last ringtone you didn't answer. Not because it was scary... Because it felt true."</p>
                <span class="quote-main-author">— Sushanth Reddy</span>
            </div>
            <div class="quotes-sub-grid">
                <div class="quote-sub-card">
