                    <span class="quote-sub-context">Raghu • Chapter 5</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-sub-card">
                    <p class="quote-sub-text">"He didn't die from suicide. He died from silence. And now he's making sure no one forgets."</p>
                    <span class="quote-sub-context">Nithya • Chapter 6</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-sub-card">
                    <p class="quote-sub-text">"Plot twist: the ghost recharges with Vi unlimited packs. Full talktime, full death-time!"</p>
                    <span class="quote-sub-context">Arjun • Chapter 3</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 6 — JOURNEY / TIMELINE SECTION -->
    <section id="journey">
        <span class="section-label">Signal Pathway</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Progressive Logs</h2>
        <div class="timeline-container">
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-node-title">01 / System Entry</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Central Counseling Mismatch</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Sushanth's electronic application parameters alter themselves, bypassing manual confirmation systems to physically bring him to RKIT.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-node-title">02 / First Frequency</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Lab Static Warning</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">Monitors flicker and crash during a baseline Java programming class, spelling out a terminal message right before a junior collapses outside.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-node-title">03 / Historical Core</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Chalkboard Discovery</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">A deep break-in past the chemistry sheds leads into the restricted exam block, confirming Karthik's direct involvement in the original 2019 device seizure.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-node-title">04 / Active Countdown</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Network Takeover</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">The curse escalates out of E-Block. Reaching a critical frequency, it writes directly on dorm room structures and overrides all global carrier systems.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
                <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                <span class="timeline-node-title">05 / Resolution Wave</span>
                <h3 class="timeline-title">The Hand-Made EMP Pulse</h3>
                <p class="timeline-desc">The investigators blast thirty seconds of absolute dead air via raw microwave components, short-circuiting the loop and releasing the underlying message.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 7 — ENDING SECTION -->
    <section id="ending">
        <div class="ending-box">
            <h2 class="ending-title">The Terminal Disconnect</h2>
            <p class="ending-reflection">
                Raghu's loop dissolved when the heavy burden of silence was broken by an explicit, long-overdue goodbye. The decaying structures of E-Block were subsequently cleared to lay down a quiet memorial garden, hosting a disconnected rotary landline that stands entirely silent. Yet, across the global framework of our connected networks, the signal leaves behind an permanent question regarding our everyday interactions.
            </p>
            <div class="ending-quote-card">
                <p class="ending-final-quote">
                    "It wasn't the phone. It was the silence that followed."
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 8 — FOOTER SECTION -->
    <footer>
        <div class="footer-title">DO NOT DISTURB</div>
        <div class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V • Interactive Storycase</div>
        <p class="footer-quote">"Some ringtones don't need a SIM to be heard."</p>
    </footer>

<script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {
            const navbar = document.querySelector('.navbar');
            const targetNavContainer = document.querySelector('.nav-links');
            const projectLinksTemplate = document.getElementById('projectNavTemplate');
            const storySection = document.querySelector('#story');
            let isMouseOverStory = false;

            // Inject your book links right into the existing navbar container pulled from the partial header
            if (targetNavContainer && projectLinksTemplate) {
                projectLinksTemplate.style.display = 'flex';
                targetNavContainer.appendChild(projectLinksTemplate);
            }

            function evaluateNavbarConfiguration() {
                if (!storySection || !navbar) return;
                
                const storyTop = storySection.getBoundingClientRect().top;
                const navbarHeight = navbar.offsetHeight;
                
                // Triggers perfectly the moment the top of the story section hits the bottom of the nav
                if (storyTop <= navbarHeight || isMouseOverStory) {
                    navbar.classList.add('show-project-nav');
                } else {
                    navbar.classList.remove('show-project-nav');
                }

                if (window.scrollY > 50) {
                    navbar.classList.add('scrolled');
                } else {
                    navbar.classList.remove('scrolled');
                }
            }
            // Scroll Monitoring
            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                evaluateNavbarConfiguration();

                // Standard highlighted section tracker logic targeting the injected list links
                if (navbar.classList.contains('show-project-nav')) {
                    const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
                    const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links-project a');
                    
                    let currentId = '';
                    sections.forEach(section => {
                        const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                        if (window.scrollY >= (sectionTop - 200)) {
                            currentId = section.getAttribute('id');
                        }
                    });

                    navLinks.forEach(link => {
                        link.classList.remove('active');
                        if (link.getAttribute('href') === `#${currentId}`) {
                            link.classList.add('active');
                        }
                    });
                }
            });

            // Hover Tracking Mechanics for the #story block
            if (storySection) {
                storySection.addEventListener('mouseenter', () => {
                    isMouseOverStory = true;
                    evaluateNavbarConfiguration();
                });

                storySection.addEventListener('mouseleave', () => {
                    isMouseOverStory = false;
                    evaluateNavbarConfiguration();
                });
            }

            // Run initial check on load execution 
            evaluateNavbarConfiguration();
        });
    </script>
    <%- include('partials/footer') %>